    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, i thought the 2016 ruling in the permanent court of arbitration basically said their claims had no legal basis? if that ruling exists, how can you say their assertions are \"legally valid\" under UNCLOS? isn't it more accurate to say they're breaking international law?",
